…Urges host communities to give CCECC construction Company maximum support. By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike on Friday, flagged off the second phase of the Sakpenwa-Bori-Kono road. The second phase of the road which gets up to Kono is 17.2km long and 22.3m wide road will have 10.65m on each lane with a 2m wide concrete median. It will have 2 bridges, 5 kms of drainage and 1,140 streetlight fittings. Wike who disclosed this in a statement released via his official twitter handle, informed that the funding of the project is guaranteed as the project is funded by an Irrevocable Standing Payment Order (ISPO) of One Billion Naira Monthly against the state’s account. He therefore called on the people of the host communities to give CCECC construction Company maximum support, adding that he looks forward to return in 14 months for the commissioning of this very important road. Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers state has revealed why he dismissed the Commissioner for Education, Dr Igbiks Tamuno. The commissioner was sacked on Tuesday for his alleged sabotage against the Rivers State Government. Shortly after signing contracts for the construction of more major roads in the state, Wike, at Government… In "News" PORT HARCOURT (Sundiata Port) - Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike has  accused Senator Magnus Abe of  embezzling N4 billion meant for the construction of critical roads and primary schools in Ogoni land, declaring that he (Wike) would complete the Kpopie-Bodo City Road abandoned by the former secretary to the  Rivers… In "Top Stories" •Governor Nyesom Wike Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers State, on Saturday, said that the decision of Southern Governors on open grazing and other issues remain irrevocable and must be respected. Wike stated this during a grand reception held in his honour by Ogoni nationality in Bori, headquarters of Khana Local… In "News"